President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to later address the nation following the meetings. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has implemented a nationwide lockdown from midnight, Thursday 26 March. The lockdown will last for 21 days. The president believes the infections rate will climb in South Africa. Ramaphosa addressed the nation on Monday after South Africa confirmed 402 positive cases of COVID-19. As the number of COVID-19 cases rises in South Africa, the government is stepping up efforts to enforce the state of national disaster. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday  Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp.